Feldon is pretty hype, Ghostly Prison was starting to creep up, as was Chaos Warp. Roc Egg getting attention is pretty neat, and the new art for Sakura-Tribe Elder is awesome
More Thespian's Stage seems like a good thing as well, and I'm really hoping to see some Ghastly Conscription's at my tables with it being in the morph deck.
Oh, and Farseek hopefully crashes again with this.
Finally, hopefully Plaguecrafter being in the commander product now finally pushes it above Fleshbag.
Storm Herd, Sun Titan, Clever Impersonator, River Kelpie, Geth, Chaos Warp, Beast Within, Garruk, Harmonize are all ones aside from stuff listed that I liked
I’m not sure if it was something you were looking to cover, but I was *not* a fan of all the recently printed cards getting a reprint, such as Zetalpa, the Lockets, and cards like those
There was a Surprising amount of cards that are still in Standard that got a reprint
People have been saying that 40 lands are “cheating” then out of reprints, I say printing Lockets instead of Signets, or other cards in Standard are depriving people of reprints that they would want.

[[Exotic Orchard]] being in all the decks makes me exceptionally happy. As does [[Sunken Hollow]], [[Prairie Stream]], and [[Cinder Glade]].  [[Ash Barrens]] was 5$ for some reason. [[Geier reach sanitarium]] is a solid reprint.
